8.9 Monthly Reporting Requirements

8.9.1 In connection with Operation, the Transporter shall prepare and submit a report to the Senders within fifteen (15) working days following the conclusion of each calendar month during which the Operation was active. The report shall detail, at a minimum:

  a. the total volumes delivered and withdrawn in Gross Standard Barrels and Net Standard Barrels;
  b. the average qualities at each Point of Entrance and Point of Exit for the relevant month;
  c. any irregularities or discrepancies that may have occurred during the course of the Operation for the given period.

This revised clause maintains the essence of the original, but slightly shifts responsibility by moving the deadline for report delivery from the tenth working day to fifteen working days after the end of the month, and it expands the content requirement to include any irregularities or discrepancies that may have occurred during the Operation. This change weakens the obligation slightly and provides the Transporter with a bit more leeway in terms of timely delivery while still ensuring adequate reporting for the Senders.
